main event: A UFO sighting occurred in Random Lake, Wisconsin on January 6, 1957, as reported by a civilian housewife.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5 minutes and involved two unidentified objects moving to the west.
The report suggests that the observed objects were partially inflated high altitude balloons, believed to be General Mills research balloons.
Handwritten annotations on the document include references to 'Division of velocity' and 'Chaotic commands'.
The report notes that there is no photograph present to accompany the observations.
The source of the report is a civilian housewife, adding to the credibility of the sighting.
sighted object: two partially inflated high altitude balloons
